Description: Egypt, elevated view of underground floor in stone wall, entrance to tomb of Amenhotep II. Metal gate covering entrance. Explanatory notice above gate. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Production place: Made in: Biban el-Muluk (Valley of the Kings - Thebes) (?)
Curator's comments: Geography: Valley of the Kings suggested by J M Hudson, 28/01/1998. However, not identified as standard location term in sources. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
